Sentencas: The cathode efficiency for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells is largely limited by the catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction.
Titulo: Highly Efficient CuCo2O4 Decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Nanostructured Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Here by, we design and synthesize CuCo2O4 decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 cathode by means of a simple gelation method and then screen-print it on scandium-stabilized zirconia electrolyte cell followed by a relatively lower temperature sintering process.
Titulo: Highly Efficient CuCo2O4 Decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Nanostructured Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The decoration of CuCo2O4 adequately enhances the electro-catalytic activity of the composite cathode for the ORR.
Titulo: Highly Efficient CuCo2O4 Decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Nanostructured Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition, Er0.4Bi1.6O3 matrix also reduces the sintering temperature (from 1000 degrees C to 850 degrees C) compared to the pristine CuCo2O4 electrode.
Titulo: Highly Efficient CuCo2O4 Decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Nanostructured Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The CuCo2O4-decorated-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 composite cathode demonstrates a lower polarization resistance (0.016 omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C) in air, exhibiting an 87% decrease in comparison to the primary CuCo2O4 cathode.
Titulo: Highly Efficient CuCo2O4 Decorated Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Nanostructured Cathode for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
